article.description: Matt Morgan scored 11 of his 17 points in the last three minutes to push Cornell past St. Peter's 65-62 Monday night.
article.headline: Cornell gets lift from Morgan in 65-62 win over St. Peter's
article.linkText: Cornell gets lift from Morgan in 65-62 win over St. Peter's
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Matt Morgan scored 11 of his 17 points in the last three minutes to push Cornell past St. Peter's 65-62 Monday night. With 5:09 left, Robert Hatter scored back-to-back layups to give Cornell a 49-47 lead. Troy Whiteside hit a 3 and, after Antwon Portley hit two free throws for the Peacocks, Morgan followed with another 3 to make it 55-49 with 3:01 to play. Quadir Welton's layup brought St. Peter's within four before Morgan made a layup and two free throws to make it 59-51 with a minute left. Chazz Patterson and Portley made back-to-back 3s to pull the Peacocks within 63-61, but they could get no closer. Morgan and Hatter combined to make 8 of 8 free throws in the final 62 seconds. Wil Bathurst led Cornell (6-6) with 18 points and Hatter added 16. Portley led St. Peter's (4-7) with 22 points. The Peacocks outrebounded Cornell 51-38.
